name: Babi Guling Slingsing "Bu Suci"
address: Jl. Raya Munggu-Kapal, Cepaka, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: Slingsing absolutely nails the textures of babi guling. The meat melts in your mouth while the skin has that perfect mix of crunch and softness.  Other places I've tried, like Pak Malen, Swarga, and Jero Kawan, can't quite compete. Plus, Slingsing's prices are fantastic, and they even offer delivery!
review 2: The Nasi Campur is great. The pork crackling is crispy. Their dish has strong taste of aromatic ginger (in Indonesia we call it kencur). The service is also good. They have a spacious car park across the street.
review 3:
The food is tasty. The parking area is spacious. The servants are helpful. There is only one main dish here, rice with mixed topping that consist of roasted pork, spicy pork (mild spicy for my tongue), and mixed vegetables. If you ask for the non spicy rice, you'll get rice with roasted pork only. So, just like the title, the protein option is only pork.
If you are hungry, you can ask for the separate rice and toppings. You also can get the mixed one for a cheaper price.
I would come to the restaurant again if I went to the area nearby the restaurant.
review 4:
The best Babi Guling joint in Bali! The crispy bits are crisp and mouthwatering savoury. The juicy meat are tender and sweet. All round delicious!

Everyone is friendly and helpful, now they have a spacious parking area across the outlet.
review 5: One of the best warung babi guling in Bali. Get the Rp40.000 portion and you won't regret it. Juicy, savoury, filling and all you ever wanted from a babi guling. Truly addicting and will recommend it to everyone.

name: Grand Srikandi Mansion Munggu
address: 94QQ+FV3, Jl. Raya Munggu-Kapal, Cepaka, Kec. Kediri, Kabupaten Tabanan, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: Paid expensive price to rent here ..And now they build business next to me , to make iron gates ..all i hear is grinding all day ..this is not a nice place to stay
review 2:
I'm renting a house here that was build only 6 months ago.. the bathroom doesn't drain water so after a shower there is water pooled on the floor all day.... This causes hundreds of flies to breed in the still water and drains.. every day I kill so many flies.

In addition, the paint they use on the house does not seal the water out, 3 weeks I to raining season and the wall are all turning yellow and growing mold, no air circulation, the walls are actually leaking water when it rains and when it rains the paint actual gets wet again and comes off when you touch...

Very poor materials and construction, I recommend you spend more money and live somewhere safe and healthy.

Same story from all the neighbors I've talked too.. if you love humidity and mold problems this is the place to live!
review 3: All buildings done wrong. No insulation from the ground, thus walls absorb surface water..no breathable membrane on the roof (under the tiles). It's mayor issue in Bali. Also roof smaller than building. Water goes inside the walls.
review 4: We bought a house after seeing it for just 15 minutes. And believe me, you never would have gotten this house at this price. Pretty neat! ü§ôüèæ

name: Lilis Ikvala Radha
address: Jl. Raya Munggu-Kapal No.12X, Abianbase, Kec. Mengwi, Kabupaten Badung, Bali 80351, Indonesia
review 1: Overall not bad experience. The room has ac, tv, hot shower, comfy bad, clean towels which is great for the price. The cons: no drinking water, leaking pipe in the bathroom, not so clean bedding, and a very noisy surroundings as the hotel is located on a busy main road. The best thing was the view from the window which surprised us in the morning. And the stuff was lovely and accommodating which is the reason why I give so many stars.
review 2:
